race.comment: ASTON JOPLIN (8) filled a minor placing last start at Bendigo behind McIvor Morgan (28.91) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form from her last run stacks up well. Must come into calculations. ZIVA BALE (5) was quickly into stride and burnt early from the middle draw where she gave a sight, finishing third (22.82) and beaten 5 lengths over 390m at Ballarat. Bold showing expected. ASTON RYAN (2) latest effort finished 4th on November 1 over 460m at this track behind Ballan Brumby beaten 5.5 lengths (26.39) in a Grade 5. Looks suited here and can measure up. ELEVATE (6) can measure up with the right run.
